# NetGame — deploy is part of every substantive change

When you finish edits that affect the live game (**`src/`**, **`server/`**, **`public/`**, **`Dockerfile`**, build config, or deps used at build time):

1. Run **`npm run build`** so `dist/index.html` matches source.
2. Run **`./deploy-remote.sh`** from **Git Bash** at the repo root when Docker and `.env` (`DEPLOY_PASSWORD`, etc.) are available.

Do **not** stop after only `npm run build`. Do **not** wait for the user to ask you to deploy.

If deploy cannot run (no Docker, no `sshpass`, missing `.env`, or SSH failure after trying fixes), say what failed and give the exact commands the operator should run.

See **[CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md)** — “Mandatory: deploy after changes”.
